oc:kn_127e8f3a a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When sending any SMS campaign or notification" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Always obtain explicit opt-in consent before sending SMS messages. Include STOP keyword in every outbound message for opt-out compliance." ;
    oc:hasRationale "TCPA and CTIA regulations require explicit consent for SMS communications. Non-compliance can result in significant fines and carrier blocking." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_12a44e00 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:KnownIssue ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When implementing Twilio Verify for two-factor authentication" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Verification code attempts must be limited (max 5 attempts with 30-minute lockout). Use 6-digit codes with 10-minute expiry for 2FA flows." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Unlimited verification attempts enable brute-force attacks. Rate limiting and short expiry protect against account takeover while maintaining usability." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_1837820e a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:RecoveryTactic ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When handling failed message deliveries" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Implement retry logic for transient delivery failures with exponential backoff. Monitor delivery status callbacks to detect and address carrier blocks or rate limiting." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Transient errors (carrier timeouts, temporary blocks) often resolve on retry. Without retry logic, deliverability suffers and campaigns underperform." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_1a368c00 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When scheduling or sending SMS campaigns" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Respect quiet hours (default 21:00–09:00 recipient timezone). Do not send messages during these periods." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Quiet hour violations trigger spam filters and carrier blocks, damaging delivery rates and sender reputation." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_73adcf0e a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before any bulk SMS campaign or when adding new recipients" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never send bulk messages without first validating phone numbers using the Twilio Lookup API to check format, activity status, and line type (landline vs mobile)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Sending to invalid or landline numbers wastes money, increases failure rates, and can flag your account for review." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_7648456b a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When scaling SMS campaigns beyond simple one-to-one messaging" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use Messaging Service SID (MG...) instead of a single phone number for high-throughput campaigns. Configure rate limiting at 10 messages/second with a daily limit of 5 per recipient." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Messaging Services provide automatic sender selection, load balancing, and compliance features that prevent carrier throttling." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_f2665b30 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When composing any SMS message content" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use template-based messages with variable substitution ({{variable}}) for consistency and testability. Keep messages under 160 characters to avoid segmentation." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Templates ensure brand consistency, make A/B testing easy, and keeping under 160 chars avoids multi-segment messages that can cause delivery issues." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

